NUMBER 30
NAME Grymwood, the burning
CALL 33
ITEM 9 963
*DESCRIPTION_START
Naught remains of this area of the forest but ash and burnt trunks, a
more recent act of nature which eradicated the foul Deep Forest. Silence
reigns here amidst the white ash, silence and the smell of burnt embers.
*DESCRIPTION_END
WASTE
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
EXIT SE 127
IFVERB SMELL -1
	ECHO PLAYER You smell ash and corruption.
	IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
		ECHO PLAYER Beneath that your wolfish senses detect the tingling scent of change.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 513
NAME Kvantar Tree
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 11
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
In the center of this wooden chamber you find the source of the red light: a
thousand tiny chips of glowing red stone embedded in the walls and floor of
the chamber. The light is unsettling in shade, though it does not hurt your
eyes at all. There seem to have been pictures on the walls once, but the
shards of stone have completely obliterated their images.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 200 VAL2=512
ITEM 1 233
ITEM 3 550 VAL2=573 UNLOCKED
ITEM 9 693
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 >= 1
		ECHO PLAYER The wisdom you have derived with study tells you that power is not all that emanates from the stone, for you also catch a hint of the sickness that the stone will bring to its worshippers.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
	ECHO PLAYER You notice the faint outline of a trapdoor in the ground.
ENDIF
;
REGIONDEF 51 DEPARTROOM 1815



